which is exactly the Laplace transform of the AWI at the test user coming from tier-$k$ BSs alone.  Utilizing this result, we have
\begin{eqnarray}
\lim_{n \ensuremath{\rightarrow} \infty} \mathcal{L}_{I_n}(s) &=& \lim_{n \ensuremath{\rightarrow} \infty} \prod_{k=1}^K \mathcal{L}_{I_n^{(k)}}(s) \nonumber  \\ 
&=& \prod_{k=1}^K \lim_{n \ensuremath{\rightarrow} \infty} \mathcal{L}_{I_n^{(k)}}(s) \nonumber \\
&=& \prod_{k=1}^K \exp \left( { - {\lambda _k}\int_0^\infty  {\int_0^\infty  {\left( {1 - {e^{ - s{{P}_{k}}hG_k\left( t \right)}}} \right)} {{\mu}_{k}}\left( t \right){q_{k}}\left( h \right)dtdh} } \right) \nonumber \\
&=& \mathcal{L}_{I_{{\ensuremath{\boldsymbol{{\lambda}}}}}}(s), 
\end{eqnarray}
which completes the proof. 
\end{IEEEproof}

